Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for such a lovely\Nintroduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It is of course a great pleasure to be\Nhere today and to meet with such a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful audience.\NWe do have some slides which will help
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.16,0:00:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,us explain things with a visual assist.\NThe information which I came upon which
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in the writing of power versus\Nforth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.76,0:00:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was an astonishing discovery.\NFor the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.71,0:00:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of human history\Nthere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.23,0:00:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved the way to discover\Ntruth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A statement that is so stunning. I'm\Nsure nobody in the audience understands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.92,0:01:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NIt took some years to recover from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Five years in which I had to decide what\Nto do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.60,0:01:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was discovered that consciousness\Nitself,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself records\Nall that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.20,0:01:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ever occurs mentally, emotionally,\Nphysically.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that has ever happened has\Nbeen recorded throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.11,0:01:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All of what we experience is time. On\Nthe level of consciousness, there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.68,0:01:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NSo everything is recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As though all of the past is present.\NWe could recover anything about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that had happened anywhere in time or\Nspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But we could not tell anything about the\Nfuture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.12,0:02:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the kinesiologic test, we could\Ndiscover anything that is or was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.36,0:02:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and but it cannot be used to foretell\Nthe future.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.92,0:02:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequence of discovering how to\Ntell truth from falsehood then ended up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in calibrating levels of consciousness\Nfrom one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.92,0:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One is bare physical existence.\NAnd we asked what is the most advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness that has ever existed\Non the planet? And we got calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,level\N1,00.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.51,0:03:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the numbers were far greater.\NTherefore, we ended up using the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.72,0:03:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithm of the number.\NWe ended up with a usable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.84,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,scale much like Fahrenheit, centigrade.\NAnybody can make up their own scale if
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they like\Non everybody's scale no matter what you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.36,0:03:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,make it there will be at a point that\Ndifferentiates truth from falsehood. So
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.08,0:03:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiologic test which I first saw\NDr. John Diamond back in the early 70s,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.31,0:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it was.\NUp to that time time, it was thought to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be a local phenomena.\NYou hold asparagus over your solar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.44,0:03:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,plexus, and if you're allergic to it,\Nyour arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.48,0:03:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was thought of as a local phenomena.\NBut by the time I saw it, I had already
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,had\Na number of rather extraordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.08,0:04:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,transformations of my own consciousness.\NAnd I saw it from a cold different
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoint.\NIt was obvious that it was the energy of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,life as consciousness that was\Nresponding to the question and not the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.92,0:04:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,individual purpose person. And so we\Nfound that the response to the kinesis
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.92,0:04:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiologic test had nothing to do with\Nthe personal opinion of the test
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.68,0:04:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,subject.\NAnd this morning we were asked to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.88,0:04:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate it. We we'll show you\Nbriefly how to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.44,0:04:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic of life that life knows\Nthat which is supportive of life and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is not much like protoplasm.\NSo it's an impersonal response much like
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.96,0:04:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,protoplasm knows that which is favorable\Nto it and that which is enimicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so using this simple test we were\Nthen able to go back over human history
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate the level of consciousness of\Nanything and everything that ever
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.36,0:05:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,existed.\NEvery writer, every philosopher, every
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.75,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual teacher, every movie, every\Nwriter, every philosopher
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we're able to do countries and\Ncontinents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What appeared then\Nis though the history of mankind was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,two-dimensional,\Nblack and white, and now we had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,three-dimensional technicolor.\NIt brought forth awarenesses
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.19,0:05:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not before possible.\NWe found that if you hold something that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is true in mind, the arm of the subject\Nthat you're using goes strong
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.72,0:05:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it's false, the arm goes weak.\NThis does not have to be verbalized. So
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan and I will show you exactly how to\Ndo it. It's very quick and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.28,0:06:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to try and complicate\Nit in your mind. It's very very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.28,0:06:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is supportive of life and\Ntrue makes you go strong. That which is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.16,0:06:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,unimicable and false allows your arm to\Ngo weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.72,0:06:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a true or false response. It's\Ntrue or not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe cannot respond with no. It\Ncan only respond to yes collapse the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.31,0:06:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,wave function\Nand the resulting der equation tells you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the new state of the universe.\NSo it coincides quite well with quant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the theory of quantum mechanics\Nand advanced theoretical physics as
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,well.\NMy own personal experiences which I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have to give you a bit otherwise some of\Nthe things I s say will sound strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll sound strange anyway, but\Nuh rather extraordinary experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,began in this lifetime what the world\Ncalls this lifetime at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.59,0:07:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three out of complete oblivion\Nfrom oblivion from absolute nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there was a\Nsevere shock like experience a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.31,0:07:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,intense awareness of existence. Out of\Nnothingness suddenly there was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. existence as such\Nthe knowingness of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which at age three was non-verbal.\NNo words for such an experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.44,0:07:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But the\Nthe confrontation with existence was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.63,0:07:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,profound and stunning.\NShortly after there suddenly came into
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness the possibility then of\Nnon-existence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that it might have come about\Nthat it might not have come about this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NAnd so there was the polarity the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,duality of existence versus\Nnon-existence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.59,0:08:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which are actually doesn't get resolved\Ntill consciousness level 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo that was the presentation of the task
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of this lifetime to transcend\Nthe ultimate truth is allness or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness.\NExistence versus non-existence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nbeyond a certain level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 600\None remembers what the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:09:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,previous lifetimes. They're not previous\Nlifetimes, but the world calls them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that. And one remember is the lifetime\Nof Hinana Buddhism in which the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.68,0:09:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reality was void.\NConsequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at each physical death, the sanity went\Ninto the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you hold in mind is what you\Nexperience.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the void is not the ultimate\Nreality. Or you could stay there. And if
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.72,0:09:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the void were the ultimate reality, who\Nwould be there to tell you about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be nothing to recall it. So the\Nconfrontation then was with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate truth. Yeah. Confrontation\Nwith what is the ultimate truth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.68,0:09:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which became something of an obsession\Nin this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:10:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as a teenager. As a teenager then I had\Na severely exhausting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.88,0:10:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,18-mi paper route in Wisconsin,\N10 below zero blizzard,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.27,0:10:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,pitch black, miles from home, no\Nelectricity on the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And to get out of the wind, I dug into a\Nbig snowbank,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,10 below zero blizzard and pitchbuck.\NSo I climbed into this hole in the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and a profound, incredible peace\Nreplaced whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.60,0:10:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion there was of a personal self.\Nan infinite exquisite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Its presence is unmistakable,\Nexquisitely gentle,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.36,0:10:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,melts. It's it melts what one thinks of\Nas oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.48,0:11:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's diff this diffuse.\NIt's like the presence of love on an
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.39,0:11:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute level\Nwhich goes on outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially\Nperhaps eons
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which I am existed\Nbefore all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.20,0:11:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and will still be here after all\Nuniverses have disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.48,0:11:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is apparently clear.\NIt's like the profound essence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.76,0:11:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness\NAnd subsequent to the experience, the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of death has never recurred,\Nincluding during the World War, World
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.48,0:11:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,War II, and minds are going off and I\Nwas on a mind sweeper and there was
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.92,0:11:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,never even the thought of death. To this\Nday, there's no thought of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.12,0:12:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no response to sudden loud\Nnoises. So, there seem to be alterations
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.07,0:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the way in which life is experienced.\NMy father came and uh our 1929 Model A
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ford\Nand uh discovered my whereabouts
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.44,0:12:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he seemed perturbed\Nand uh I realized that if I didn't come
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the body and breathe again, if I\Ndidn't breathe the body, there was no
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.24,0:12:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to breathe the body.\NIn fact, there hasn't been any desire to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.56,0:12:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,breathe it since. But anyway, breathe\NI saw that he believed in death. Oh, and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.95,0:12:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that if I didn't rep breathe and\Nreenergize
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the body, whatever you want to call it,\Nthat he would think I had died. They
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would take away the body and bury it and\Nmy father would grieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.80,0:13:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I love my father a great deal. And\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.00,0:13:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I I made the mistake\Nof breathing the body again and saved
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,him the grief.\NAnyway, that was so there was a series
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.16,0:13:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of such experiences, you know,\Nand um that led to sort of we'll skip
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,over a number of such experiences but\Nthere was always difficulty in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.27,0:13:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maintaining a sense of a personal self\Nbecause it kept dissolving into an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.48,0:13:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite presence and I would have to\Nfocus on being Dave and you're sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.07,0:13:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,here in this chair in this classroom\Nand hanging hang on to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.36,0:13:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the personal self, you know, which\Nseemed elusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there seemed to be I was a very\Nreligious young man uh brought up by
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:14:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Episcopal, very very religious\Nand scrupulous in fact. And one day uh
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at some time in my early life, I was\Nwalking along in the woods. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.48,0:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely beautiful and still.\NAnd suddenly out of nothingness, out of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness\Narose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.68,0:14:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a revelation, a comprehension\Nof the totality of the suffering of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.44,0:14:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind\Nthroughout all of time in its totality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.60,0:14:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of its agony and fear and\Nsuffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's it was stunning.\NAnd in that instant, I became an
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,atheist.\NI held God responsible for the totality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of human suffering\Ninstead of the human ego. But at that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:15:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,time, I did not understand that.\NI thought God created everything. 1930s
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,religion. That would be a common belief\Nsystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.92,0:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody spoke about the ego. They only\Nspoke about sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.92,0:15:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I didn't realize that the ego was\Nthis was the creation of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.76,0:15:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I became an atheist and frankly\Nit was a great relief to get away from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.83,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sin.\NYou didn't worry that a passing thought
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.27,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,might condemn you to hell forever. You\Nknow, it was quite a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.48,0:15:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a devout atheist.\NI went to a Jesuit university and got
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:16:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,straight A in theology,\Nethics, metaphysics, the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.32,0:16:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But that wasn't satisfying. Later on, I\Nwent through psychoanalysis. I became a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.19,0:16:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist.\NI had in fact the largest psychiatric
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.16,0:16:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,practice in the United States.\N2,000 outpatients, thousand new patients
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a year,\N50 employees, 25 offices,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.95,0:16:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,electrophilographic laboratory, clinical\Nlaboratory, research laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.16,0:16:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We had one of the few first computers\Navailable. It was a giant thing. It
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,stood in a room of itself. We used to\Ngenulect to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Had to be air conditioned, special\Ncables of electric.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.19,0:16:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wondrous machine\Nto do our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.00,0:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, all of this\Nintensity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the essential core and truth\Nof existence persisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:17:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nit finally
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.72,0:17:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,this huge practice\Nuh and the seeing of thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,patients thousands of patients\Nin the most severe conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh eventually the the pressure of trying\Nto help so many people, I began to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,develop all kinds of psychosmatic\Nillnesses.
