Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.76,0:35:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's twice the pip."\NHer customers come back to her and want
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.28,0:35:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to sit at her table. She's friendly and\Nnice. She remembers her name. She
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.32,0:35:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes Georgette or whatever her name\Nis. You know, you look forward to seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.40,0:35:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,her. So you see how new energy has the\Nbeginning of love is beginning to show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.48,0:35:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up as this willingness\Nand acceptance is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.00,0:35:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,now where you begin to realize that you\Nare the source of the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.88,0:35:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,details of your own life. You stop\Nblaming it on others. Down below people
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.68,0:35:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,blame everything. You slip on the ice is\NGimble's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.72,0:35:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> As you get a little bit higher, you\Nrealize you you're careless in where you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.76,0:35:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,put your feet. Frankly,\Nso you begin to accept responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.48,0:35:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the beginning of real power.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.52,0:36:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if we calibrate companies and uh we we\Nrecently we calibrate thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.04,0:36:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,things you know and uh recently we did\Nall the giant the biggest corporations
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.35,0:36:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world you know biggest\Ncorporations in the world biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.72,0:36:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,corporations in America and Fortune\Nmagazine
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.07,0:36:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we've done all the departments of all\Nthe various governments etc. And rather
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.80,0:36:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing facts begin to reveal themselves\Nthat almost all the giant corporations
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.40,0:36:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world uh calibrate maybe 205.\NFierce you find anything. What does that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.76,0:36:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? Reliable, dependable. You paid\N$20,000 for a car, you get a car. You
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.72,0:36:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,get a guaranteed car. You don't get a\Nfake car.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.72,0:36:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what you paid for. So there's\Nintegrity, honesty. Most government
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.48,0:36:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,agencies calibrate around 205. You see,\Nthat's not airy fairy. It's not lovey.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.92,0:36:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not romantic.\NBut that isn't what you're paying for.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.07,0:37:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Invest your money in a stock. Say, "I\Nwant profit." So
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.76,0:37:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you get higher than that, then you have\Nto add a new element.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.59,0:37:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,friendliness, integrity,\Nwilling to stand by your product, give
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.48,0:37:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you back your money smilingly, no\Nquestions asked. That's how I got
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.16,0:37:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,corresponding with Cam Sam Walton.\NYeah, here was Sam Walden
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.07,0:37:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,establishing a business based on certain\Npremises which are generally considered
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.88,0:37:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual, you know, and so we\Ncorresponded back and forth. And in the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.68,0:37:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,book, Harvard versus Forest, you know, I\Ncalibrated Walmart at 385 or 365, I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,forget what it was.\NThat's not staggeringly high when you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.76,0:37:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,compare it to a saint, but Walmart is\Nnot doesn't claim to be a saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.20,0:37:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 365 and it's gone down somewhat\Nsince Saman died, but still it's way up
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.92,0:37:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there. There's nothing in its class. You\Nknow, all the corporations in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.83,0:38:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is in the 300. Nothing is really\Nin high 200. Only Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.20,0:38:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does that demonstrate to us? I\Ndon't care anything about Walmart
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.35,0:38:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,personally. Is that integrity that\Nintegrity then shows up in every area of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.48,0:38:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\NSo here was a corporation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.52,0:38:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,whose integrity was remarkable. That's\Nwhy I remarked about it in power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.52,0:38:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,force. And now we see what integrity has\Nbrought about that integrity. It is now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.52,0:38:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the largest corporation in the entire\Nworld. The largest corporation in the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.48,0:38:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,entire world\Nand also the highest calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.35,0:38:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness of an enterprise of a\Ncorporate nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.20,0:38:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrating that that the power of\Nintegrity shows up on the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.64,0:38:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not some kind of airy fairy\Ndoer
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.48,0:39:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,goody two shoes kind of fantasy.\NYou see the hardboiled businessman a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.59,0:39:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual concept sounds a little\Nairy fairy touchy feely. Don't give me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.32,0:39:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,any touchy feely. Please give me a\Nbreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.68,0:39:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, caringness, consideration,\Nfriendliness, and what does the jacket
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.72,0:39:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,say when you walk into Walmart? Says,\N"How can I help?" Right out of the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.00,0:39:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,helpfulness, willingness.\NAll right. So, then we finally get to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.16,0:39:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reason and logic. This is where\NNorthern Europe, the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.24,0:39:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced civilized countries calibrated\Nin the 400s. This is the power of the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.83,0:39:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect.\NThe great benefit of the intellect of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.32,0:39:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,course we witness every day as the\Nadvances of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.76,0:39:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Few of us would be alive. We'd all be\Ndead of various diseases. And because of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.48,0:40:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,science, all the diseases I treated when\NI first started in medicine some 50
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.56,0:40:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago no longer even exist.\NThe infectious disease hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.44,0:40:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people sick and dying of various\Ndiseases, there no antibiotics, no way
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.52,0:40:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to cure them.\NNowadays all those people would be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.96,0:40:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,living you know. So the 400s is the\Nworld of the intellect, the university,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the college professor. The 400s are\Npresidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.64,0:40:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,statesmen,\NSupreme Court justices,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.24,0:40:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,professors, Nobel Prize winners,\Nusually the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.28,0:40:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To be president of a huge\Ncountry then requires
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.20,0:40:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual fortitude, vers.\NSo they almost all do. All the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.32,0:41:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,presidents throughout time have been in\Nthe high 400
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.40,0:41:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from 500.\NFrom 500 up from 500 up, a person
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.56,0:41:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be interested in being\Npresident.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.68,0:41:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and up then is the opening of the\Nheart chakra
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.04,0:41:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the energy field of love starts\Ncalibrating at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.56,0:41:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540\Nis the level of unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The level 500 and up in itself is rare.\N4% of the population ever calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.11,0:41:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,500.\N0.4
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.40,0:41:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 540.\NUnconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.40,0:41:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show the distribution of the\Nlevels of consciousness in the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.68,0:41:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,population in the next slide.\NLove becomes then progressively
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.83,0:41:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional,\Nfinally saintly and at the level 600 the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.52,0:42:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self\Ndissolves into a oneness and that is the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.16,0:42:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,state of enlightenment. The states of\Nenlightenment begin at 600. What the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.88,0:42:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world calls enlightenment happens one in\N10 million lifetimes. One in 10 million
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.28,0:42:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ever reaches 600. And of those who do,\Nonly half will stay in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.76,0:42:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In that condition,\Nthere's no need to breathe or to eat or
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.40,0:42:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to move. It is absolutely perfect,\Ncomplete, and still.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.31,0:42:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond time, beyond description.\NThere's no thinkingness, no thought, no
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.59,0:42:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,desire for anything.\NPeople
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.48,0:42:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,do strange things. They want you to eat\Nand all kinds of oddities
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.31,0:42:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which to them seem important. They see\Nit's important to them. They eat because
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.83,0:42:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important to them because otherwise\Nthe body falls over which is irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.35,0:43:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way.\NGood ridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.92,0:43:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As love becomes more perfected. And one\Ncomes into
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.24,0:43:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,various progressive states which are\Nfamiliar to saintthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.20,0:43:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a state of\Nat about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.48,0:43:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One falls in love with everything and\Neveryone. The beauty of everything and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.31,0:43:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,its perfection shines forth. Everyone is\Nboth either handsome or beautiful as the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.07,0:43:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,case may be or both\Nhandsome and beautiful and beautifully
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.64,0:43:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,handsome.\NOne falls in love with everyone and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.72,0:43:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everything all of life. And you see what\Nis emerging then is the awareness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.72,0:44:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of all of life.\NAnd porn develops a certain reverence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.11,0:44:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of love we're speaking of is\Nnot what the world calls love. What the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.80,0:44:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,world calls love is an emotion, an\Nemotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.59,0:44:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which goes from here to there. I love\Nyou. You love me. Okay? Which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.72,0:44:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,setup for murder and suicide as you can\Nsee.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.04,0:44:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I love you and you love me, I\Nwill kill you or kill myself. So murder
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.00,0:44:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and suicide is the downside of that kind\Nof love which is also conditional.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.92,0:44:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. The kind of love we're\Ntalking about then is a way of being in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.56,0:44:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.\NAt 540 that calibrated level,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.04,0:44:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,love is what one is, what one has\Nbecome.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.40,0:45:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no love that goes from here\Nto there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.88,0:45:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the condition in which you\Nexperience the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.92,0:45:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, there's a reverence for\Nand a respect for all of life in all of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.88,0:45:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,its expressions.\NAs the love advances, it comes to a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.72,0:45:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,state\Nwhich can only be called ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.88,0:45:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the higher level of love to even look\Nat two people who are affectionate
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.80,0:45:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,towards the each other, you can break\Nout in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.04,0:45:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You break out in tears. So there's a\Nperiod in which you cry at everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.24,0:45:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every kind gesture mother reaches over,\Ntouch your crying child, and comfort it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.00,0:45:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And you break out in tears. Everything\Nmakes you break out in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.31,0:45:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to listen to beautiful music\Nbecause you cry all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.35,0:46:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that there's a level of love\Nwhich can only be described as ecstatic
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.07,0:46:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,described by Rama Krishna\Nexperienced in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.76,0:46:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,one of absolute ecstasy beyond\Ndescription
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.76,0:46:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in which it's impossible almost not to\Ndance physically
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.88,0:46:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or psychically One is in\Necstasy at the re revelation of the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.35,0:46:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God is all existence\Necstatic when it first reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.48,0:46:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to function in that\Nstate of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.76,0:46:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nby divine inspiration one may surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.20,0:46:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it to God.\NOne surrenders the ecstasy to God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.88,0:47:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then in its place\Nis a profound and infinite peace with no
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.28,0:47:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning and no end.\NPeace of God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.56,0:47:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this day.\NGo to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.16,0:47:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Thank you.\NThis is the distribution of the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.11,0:47:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.\NYou see, your expectations of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.48,0:47:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have never been tailored by any kind of\Nrealistic expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.52,0:47:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, this is the distribution of the\Nlevels of consciousness throughout all
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.76,0:47:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of humanity.\NAnd now one can revise one's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.31,0:47:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations.\NAt the time of the Neanderthal man
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.52,0:47:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level was about 75.\NHow many kept evolving off the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.52,0:48:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it got up into the low 400s. At\Nthe time of the birth of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.88,0:48:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of all of\Nmankind stood at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.07,0:48:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of the birth of Jesus\NChrist, the consciousness level of all
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.44,0:48:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind stood at 100.\NThroughout the ensuing centuries, the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.44,0:48:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of man crept up. and\Nthen for the last thousand years stood
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.72,0:48:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,at 190\Nstalled out at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.55,0:48:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask what was it in the 1400s,\Nwe'll get 190. What was it in the 1500s?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.52,0:48:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it in the 1600s?\NThe time which some of these many of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.64,0:48:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,these buildings here were built in the\N1600s.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.24,0:48:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind was\N190.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.64,0:49:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's below truth, below integrity.\NYou know, and so the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.59,0:49:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is bloody and savage.\NThe history of Europe is bloody
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.80,0:49:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,savagery.\NFirst, this side wars and butchers them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.11,0:49:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This side wars and butchers that. Then\Nthey get busy beheading each other. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.44,0:49:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a bloody and horrible history. Look at\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.72,0:49:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last century,\N10 million people have died of this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.31,0:49:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million rather. Sorry, forgot one.\NZero.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.00,0:49:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million. Right.\NThen in the late 1980s,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.96,0:49:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for unknown reasons,\Nthe consciousness level of mankind went
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.96,0:49:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from 190 to 207.\NThe most important phenomena in human
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.40,0:49:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,history. really\Nto go from non- integrity that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.80,0:49:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive. At 190 eventually mankind\Nwould have destroyed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.76,0:50:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russians were prepared to do it,\Nweren't they? The great mega bomb that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.35,0:50:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,would kill all of life on the planet\Nforever. Radioactivity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.24,0:50:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,death to humanity by radioactivity.\NNot too kindly a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.04,0:50:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe we escaped.\NSo in the late 1980s the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.72,0:50:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,level of mankind went up to 207.\NCritical critical because 207 you go
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.11,0:50:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,strong with kines theology. At 190 you\Ngo weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.04,0:50:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207 there's hope. At 190 the fate of\Nmankind would be eventually its own
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.64,0:50:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,obliteration.\NThe only reason mankind didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.92,0:50:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,obliterate itself until now it didn't\Nhave anything capable big enough to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.24,0:50:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody all at once.\NSo the Russians were busy working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.40,0:50:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We would have eventually done it. All\Nright. So here we see the distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.55,0:51:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind. We see that 78% of the\Nworld's population at this time 78%
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.16,0:51:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates below 200. to see if that's\Nstill affect
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.11,0:51:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,um we have permission to ask it to you.\NAnd approximately 78% of those
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.88,0:51:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,population covers below 200 at this\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.68,0:51:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly,\Nyou know the implications of that alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.44,0:51:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world's population\Nis not integrate
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.52,0:51:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,believes in falsehood\Nand will kill you if you don't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.76,0:51:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in it falsehood.\NAll right? So that's where mankind has
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.88,0:51:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved to at the present time.\NYou might say the collective good karma
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.92,0:52:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind has brought about a\Nprogression of the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.24,0:52:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's at a hopeful 207.\NMaybe we could have the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.35,0:52:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nthe big difficulty in the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.31,0:52:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is called duality. The\Npathway I teach is devotional
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.92,0:52:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,nonduality.\Ndevotion to God, to the truth of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.96,0:52:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and transcending the dualistic nature of\Nthe ego, at which point the mind goes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.44,0:52:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,silent.\NThe idea of duality is that there are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.68,0:52:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,two opposite things. You see, there's\Nheat and cold. There's goodness and
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.59,0:52:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,badness.\NPolitical left, political right,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.88,0:52:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything gets into a polarized\Nduality. Consequently, conflict and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.04,0:52:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,H the right versus the wrong.\NOne day I'm right, you're wrong. Next
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.04,0:53:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,day we trade off. Right?\NYou look at time, the right and the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.88,0:53:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. If there are two different lights\Nand you look at the map of the world as
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.07,0:53:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it evolves over the centuries, you see\Nright and wrong, right and wrong, right
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.44,0:53:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrong. See it all flashing on at\Nall. This side's right, this side's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.20,0:53:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. Now two years later, this side's\Nwrong. This side's right. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.76,0:53:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in World War II. So they were our\Nenemies. We hated them. We was to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.80,0:53:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,their terrible Japs, etc. Show them a\Ngleaming teeth. Evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.44,0:53:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now\Nafter the war, see the veterans on both
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.00,0:53:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,sides are great buddies. We love each\Nother.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.64,0:53:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I salute his bravery. He salutes my\Nbravery. We both realize we did it for
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.16,0:53:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the sake of what we believed in.\NThe commitment was to integrity. What we
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.44,0:53:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,thought of as integrity at the time.\NHuh? So that heals the disparity. We
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.40,0:54:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't hate anybody anymore. They don't\Nhate us. And veterans of both sides pray
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.48,0:54:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,together, meet together, embrace each\Nother, and we realize the dignity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.04,0:54:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the commitment to something greater\Nthan oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.96,0:54:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One may be mistaken at the time, but\Nyou'll find that a kamicazi pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.00,0:54:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates quite high.\NHe did what he did because of his belief
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.11,0:54:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the divinity of his emperor.\NAll right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.64,0:54:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see from an arbitrary viewpoint,\Nwe think there's hot and cold. Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.64,0:54:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only the presence of heat.\NThere's either heat present or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.28,0:54:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable, not two\Nvariables. Heat is either present or not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.07,0:54:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,present.\NNext we can look at another scale
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.20,0:54:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,example two in which you see to want a\Nthing or not want a thing. Then you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.07,0:54:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,perceive a projected value which you\Nproject upon the thing. It's either
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.64,0:55:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,precious and worthwhile or it's useless.\NIf you love gold, you'll kill for it. If
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.40,0:55:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it's just sort of a, you know,\Npretty and useful, you won't be bothered
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.00,0:55:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's just sort of okay. It's\Nneutral. Gold means neut neutral. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.68,0:55:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,either good or bad. It's sort of it's\Nuseful. You stick things in it. Okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.72,0:55:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have the next one.\NAgain, another examples of duality. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.24,0:55:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,goodness versus badness\Nare all perceptual. Well, they say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.83,0:55:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,perceptual. The difficulty with the\Ndualistic mind is that it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.68,0:55:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has these belief systems which it then\Nprojects upon the world and says and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.80,0:55:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks it sees it out there. It exists\Nonly within your mind. Doesn't exist in
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.07,0:55:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. Just as causality is an\Nexplanation made up by the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.28,0:56:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, evolution and creation are one\Nand the same thing. If things don't come
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.64,0:56:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,about by virtue of cause, then how do\Nthey come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.31,0:56:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the existence of God, because\Nof the source of existence itself
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.44,0:56:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the great infinite power, then\Nthe potentiality of each thing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.52,0:56:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to manifest its own actuality\Nunfolds.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.55,0:56:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing causing it to unfold.\NThe source of that which one witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.35,0:56:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is a is the presence of divinity as the\Nsource of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.04,0:56:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The power\Nto bring forth your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.11,0:56:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be found within the conceptual\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.88,0:57:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality then by its karmic\Npropensity unfolds as an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.31,0:57:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing it to do so.\NThe idea of cause is a mentation in your
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.07,0:57:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,mind.\NThere's nothing causing this to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.07,0:57:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,whatsoever.\NThe potentiality to use the body to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.16,0:57:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,explain\Na dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.31,0:57:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,does this of its own. I have nothing to\Ndo with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.35,0:57:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm as surprised by what the hand does\Nas you are. I don't know what it's doing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.40,0:57:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there. It's trying to explain something.\NThe potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.52,0:57:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is karmically balanced under the right\Ncondition becomes has the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.48,0:57:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,then to become an actuality.\NAnd so what seems to be sequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.92,0:58:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's sequential is\Nperception. Because your perception goes
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.07,0:58:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from here to there. You think things are\Nhappening sequentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.72,0:58:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The witnessing is what is sequential.\NThe actuality is outside of time to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.40,0:58:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,begin with.\NIf this were not so,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.96,0:58:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no one here would exist.\NLet's see if that's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.52,0:58:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes composity.\NYes, what we said is a fact that things
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.31,0:58:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,come into actuality out of their\Npotentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.55,0:58:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the presence of the infinite\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.31,0:58:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite power of divinity is the\Nonly possible source of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.83,0:59:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we just got rid of\Nduality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.68,0:59:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll move to the next exciting.\NAh
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.79,0:59:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,people say well I can't get rid of my\Nmind. I meditate. I'm a Buddhist. I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.88,0:59:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this. I'm that. I want to transcend the\Nmind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.79,0:59:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well we have lots of good news this\Nmorning. The other good news is that 98%
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.07,0:59:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of your mind is silent at all times.\NIn fact, right this moment, every single
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.20,0:59:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,mind in this realm is silent.\NAll you have to do is fall back into the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.16,0:59:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,silence. You see that the silence is\Nalready in existence just prior to the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.68,0:59:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thought.\NI was telling somebody this morning, the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.35,0:59:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha and I often have arguments about\Nthings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.96,0:59:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Buddha believes that reality be\Ncan can be glimpsed between two
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.64,0:59:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts.\NNo, it's not between two thoughts. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.88,1:00:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to the thought.\NJust prior to the thought
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.88,1:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is a space of infinite silence out of\Nwhich thinking arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.92,1:00:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That which out of which it arises is\Nsilent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.07,1:00:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, your mind right now is silent.\NThe mind of everyone in this room is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.59,1:00:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,currently silent.\NThere is a focus. It's like a huge
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.55,1:00:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,coliseum. Everybody's gone. It's\Ncompletely empty. And over in the corner
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.48,1:00:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the coliseum, there's a 4x5 in black\Nand white TV set. And you're focused on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.28,1:00:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this. You think the coliseum is busy and\Nnoisy. It's empty and silent just
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.44,1:00:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're focused on this little\Nscreen over in the corner of the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.24,1:00:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,coliseum.\NSo we what we discovered is that your
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.04,1:00:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is silent. 98% of the work you need\Nto become a enlightened is already done.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.79,1:01:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You've only got 2% left.\NSnap. Right. Anybody can have 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.07,1:01:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go. Wanting to think, wanting to\Ngo. So, we see that one is addicted to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.96,1:01:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking this. And the real secret, the\Nreal secret
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.64,1:01:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you become hypnotized by the 1%\Nthat's talking
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.83,1:01:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one or 2%.\NYou are in a state of self hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.48,1:01:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a secret out of which a lot of\Nyou will move rapidly. There's only one
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.24,1:01:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or 2% is busy.\NIt's in a hypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.16,1:01:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that is needed then is to\Nrealize that and once you realize it,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.11,1:01:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not that difficult to let go of the\Ndesire for the thinkingness and all
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.68,1:01:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's derived out of it. What is the\Npayoff that you get from the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.59,1:02:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go of the ego and have a silence\Nreplace it? It is only necessary to see
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.16,1:02:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what the ego is up to and be willing to\Nsurrender its payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.52,1:02:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego because it is not based on\Nreality or love has managed to juice
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.35,1:02:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pain and suffering.\NSo the ego lives off the non-lo
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.40,1:02:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,non-reality\Nthen of pain, suffering, guilt, feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.72,1:02:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,right, feeling righteous.\NAnd you see what it does? It I it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.59,1:02:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,polarizes everything. It politicizes\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.24,1:02:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can be contentious and feel so\Ngood and so right and see how wrong the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.83,1:02:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other people are and feel innocent as\Nyou plunge a dagger into their heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.88,1:02:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're evil because you\Nmoralize
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.24,1:02:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're they're evil. And why\Nare they evil? Because you idealize
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.59,1:03:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you hypothesize that they could be\Nbetter. And then we romanticize. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.24,1:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what a wonderful world if everybody\Nwould just see things the way I see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.28,1:03:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't, of course. So that's why\Nwe criticize and we feel upset about
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.11,1:03:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that. So we emotionalize. We have a\Nparade. We dramatize it. We make movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.68,1:03:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have parades. It's catastrophic.\NCatastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.48,1:03:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at any point in history,\Nincluding the present time, and discover
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.03,1:03:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's catastrophic.\NIt's catastrophic right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.24,1:03:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you haven't noticed.\NSo we theorize that it could be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.96,1:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,differently. Could be different. We\Nrationalize why it's not different.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.88,1:03:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we don't have the time. We don't\Nhave the tax money. We fantasize how it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.11,1:03:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,could be.\NWe go on, we infantalize things,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.52,1:03:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectualize it. And of course,\Nbasically what we're doing is
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.79,1:03:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalizing it. We idealize it and then\Nwe glamorize the whole thing. Aren't our
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.55,1:04:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,ideas wonderful? We dramat make a drama.\Nand make a huge movie, $45 million, so
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.79,1:04:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can see how I think or feel\Nabout something. The egoentricity of all
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.35,1:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is just staggering. All of this is\Negoentricity and nothing but
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.24,1:04:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who cares what your views are. I don't.\NDoes anybody else? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.28,1:04:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time you get into a discussion with\Nsomebody, take a moment and notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.28,1:04:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they really don't give a rap what you're\Nthinking or what your opinions are. They
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.76,1:04:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,really don't care. You see, if you\Npresent them with a platform,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.64,1:04:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you present them with a platform from\Nwhich their ego can grandstand, they can
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.88,1:04:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,pontificate,\Nthen they love you. If you don't give
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.96,1:04:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,them a platform upon which to\Npontificate, they consider you boring
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.52,1:05:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will demonize you on top of\Nthat as being bad and evil and ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.76,1:05:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we prize many things out\Nof the solar plexus. We're willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.92,1:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifice a great deal for materialism.\NAnd the latest craze in society is to be
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.52,1:05:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim.\NThe competition in victimhood is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.83,1:05:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous.\NThere's no aspect of human life that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.88,1:05:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,can't be portrayed as some kind of\Nvictimization,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.64,1:05:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which means there are evil people out\Nthere victimizing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.68,1:05:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People victimize me all the time.\NThey do it all day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.72,1:05:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think you're being victimized.\NYou just haven't noticed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.59,1:05:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Every move you're being a victim of\Nsomething or someone,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.48,1:06:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the government, of course.\NNext, we're going to be through in about
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.92,1:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,2 minutes. We will end abruptly. The\Nspeaker will turn quickly on his heel
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.00,1:06:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk away. Then you'll know that's\Nthe end.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.83,1:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to just compare. Reality is\Nviewed from the from the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.00,1:06:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoint of causality. The Newtonian\Ncharacteristic world of science, the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.48,1:06:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect and logic which is on the left\Nhand side. Everything is logical,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.76,1:06:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,limitable, limited, provable\Nto a greater closer to reality. In
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.11,1:06:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics, things are\Nlikelihood. They're not certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.64,1:06:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Provability is a figment of your own\Nimagination. I'll tell you nothing can
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.55,1:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,be proven. Nothing is proof of all is\Nnot capacity. Why is that so? Because
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.96,1:06:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate reality is subjectivity.\NNothing can be true. And in the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.24,1:06:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian paradigm,\Nit can only be realized
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.52,1:07:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectively\Nas the sense of the source of one's own
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.92,1:07:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NYou cannot prove the existence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.00,1:07:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ridiculous.\NThe person who lives the scientific
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.64,1:07:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,objective intellectual world says that\Nthat is the only world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.52,1:07:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know why they say that? Because\Nsubjectively that's the truth to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.00,1:07:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute truth then as you go beyond\Ntheology, epistemology, all of it. You
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.03,1:07:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,end up with the radical truth is subject\Nsubjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.48,1:07:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the sense of awareness of your\Nexistence that is listening to the voice
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.31,1:07:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment. The sense of reality, the\Nsource of one's own existence is the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.76,1:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God within.\NAnd when you say I, it's
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.92,1:07:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by permission of the divinity within.\NYou might say permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.03,1:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the right word. By virtue of the\Npresence
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.83,1:08:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of God within, one knows that one's\Nexists.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.24,1:08:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One is aware of one's existence.\NAnd to know that that source of one's
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.31,1:08:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,existence is the truth of who one is\Nis what is meant by self-realization.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.27,1:08:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank you.
